1. To bring Wi-Fi, the following package should be installed: `bcmwl-kernel-source`
   which is command:

    ```
    sudo apt install bcmwl-kernel-source
    ```

2. Volume control doesn't work. Refer to https://askubuntu.com/a/922795/732512

3. If Bluetooth audio output device could be paired but not connected.

   If you get the following error when trying to connect to a bluetooth audio output,
   then install `pulseaudio-module-bluetooth` package as instructed in [1]

        DBusFailedError: Protocol not available ...

   Installation:

        `sudo apt install pulseaudio-module-bluetooth`

   [1]: https://github.com/blueman-project/blueman/issues/547#issuecomment-231644285
